  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (94ae897 2023-10-31T00:17:29.299689000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nAfter the last nightly release I realized that there is a difference between running commands in Linux vs Mac\r\n\r\nFor example trying to run a non-existen binary using `tryFfi`\r\n\r\nError message in linux:\r\n```\r\nfailed to execute command cd \"/home/foo/bar\" && \"foo\": No such file or directory (os error 2)\r\n```\r\n\r\nError message in mac:\r\n```\r\nFailed to execute command \"foo\": No such file or directory (os error 2)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn Linux `tryFfi` always uses a `cd /current/dir` and then it tries to execute the actual command while on Mac it just tries to executes the command right away.\r\n\r\nNot sure if this is intended or a bug",
